		<body>
			<div type="leaf">
				<pb facs="#f026"/>
				<metamark change="#StB" facs="#f026_z026" function="folio" n="25"
					place="top right margin" rend="pencil">folio number 25</metamark>
				<p>be amazed at the wondrous ability of those<lb/>
					<del change="#StC" facs="#f026_z024" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">now
						</del><del change="#StC" facs="#f026_z023" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke"
						>half-forgotten</del>
					<add change="#StC" facs="#f026_z022" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">Anaks
						of </add><metamark change="#StC" facs="#f026_z025" function="caret"
						place="below" rend="caret">caret</metamark>men<add change="#StBa"
						facs="#f026_z061" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> and
					shocked at this renewed<lb/> example of the fact<add change="#StBa"
						facs="#f026_z060" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> that
					Fortune has more to do with<lb/> fame than merit, -- though<add change="#StBa"
						facs="#f026_z058" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> without
						merit<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z057" hand="#HM" place="inline"
						rend="no_caret">, </add>lasting fame there can be none<add change="#StBa"
						facs="#f026_z056" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">.</add><lb/></p>
				<p>Nevertheless<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z055" hand="#HM" place="inline"
						rend="no_caret">,</add> it would argue too illy of my country<lb/> were this
					maxim to hold good concerning Nathaniel<lb/> Hawthorne<add change="#StBa"
						facs="#f026_z053" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">, </add>a
						man<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z052" hand="#HM" place="inline"
						rend="no_caret">,</add> who already<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z054"
						hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> in some few minds<add
						change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z051" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret"
							>,</add><lb/> has shed <quote change="metadata#readingNH" facs="#f026_z050">"such a light<add change="#StC" facs="#f026_z050"
						hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> as never illuminates the
					earth,<lb/> save when a great heart burns as the household fire<lb/> of a grand
					intellect."<lb/></quote></p>
				<p>The words are his,<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z021" hand="#HM" place="inline"
						rend="no_caret"/><corr change="#StE" facs="#f026_z021" rend="#comp"
						>"</corr><add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z021" hand="#HM" place="inline"
						rend="no_caret">-- </add>in the <corr change="#StE" facs="#f026_z021"
						rend="#comp">"</corr>Select Party<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z020"
						hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">";</add> and they<lb/><metamark
						change="#StE" facs="#f026_z062" function="x" place="margin left"
						rend="pencil">compositor's "x"</metamark> are a magnificent setting to a
						<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z019" hand="#EM" place="inspace"
						rend="no_caret">coincident sentiment </add>of<lb/> my own<add change="#StBa"
						facs="#f026_z048" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> but <del
						change="#StC" facs="#f026_z018" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">feebly
						</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f026_z016" hand="#HM" place="above"
						rend="caret"><del change="#StC" facs="#f026_z016" hand="#HM"
							rend="single-stroke">irr </del></add><add change="#StC"
						facs="#f026_z015" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">ramblingly</add>
					<metamark change="#StC" facs="#f026_z017" function="caret" place="inline"
						rend="caret">caret with guideline</metamark>expressed yesterday<add
						change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z047" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,
					</add>in reference to him<lb/>self<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z046"
						hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">.</add> Gainsay it who will<add
						change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z045" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret"
						>,</add> as I now write<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z044" hand="#HM"
						place="inline" rend="no_caret">, </add>I am <add change="#StBa"
						facs="#f026_z014" hand="#HM" place="inspace" rend="no_caret"
					>P</add>osterity<lb/> speaking by proxy<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z043"
						hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret"> -- </add>and after times will
					make it more<lb/> than good<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z042" hand="#HM"
						place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> when I declare <add change="#StBa"
						facs="#f026_z041" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">--</add> that
					the American<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z040" hand="#HM" place="inline"
						rend="no_caret">, </add>who up<lb/> to the present day<add change="#StBa"
						facs="#f026_z039" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> has
						evinced<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z038" hand="#HM" place="inline"
						rend="no_caret">,</add> in Literature<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z037"
						hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> the largest<lb/> brain
						<del change="#StC" facs="#f026_z011" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">and
						</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f026_z012" hand="#HM" place="above"
						rend="caret">with </add><metamark change="#StC" facs="#f026_z013"
						function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">caret</metamark>the largest
						heart<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z036" hand="#HM" place="inline"
						rend="np_caret">,</add> that man is Nathaniel<lb/> Hawthorne<add
						change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z035" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">.
						</add>Moreover<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z034" hand="#HM"
						place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> that whatever Nathaniel
					Hawthorne<lb/> may hereafter write<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z033"
						hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> "The Mosses from an Old
					Manse" will<lb/>
					<metamark change="#StB" facs="#f026_z032" function="confirm" place="margin left"
						rend="x">x</metamark><add change="StBa" hand="#HM" place="inline"
						rend="no_caret">be</add> ultimately accounted his masterpiece<add
						change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z031" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret">.
					</add>For there is<lb/> a sure<add change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z030" hand="#HM"
						place="inline" rend="no_caret">,</add> though a secret sign in some works
					which <lb/>prove the culmination of the powers <metamark change="#StC"
						facs="#f026_z010" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">caret with
						guideline</metamark>
					<add change="#StC" facs="#f026_z009" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">(only
						the developable ones, however)</add> that produced <lb/>them<add
						change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z029" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret"
						>.</add> But I am by no means desirous of the <lb/>glory of a prophet<add
						change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z028" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret"
						>.</add> I pray Heaven that Hawthorne may <lb/><metamark change="#StBa"
						facs="#f026_z008" function="underline" place="below" rend="no_caret"
						>underline</metamark>yet prove me an impostor in this prediction<add
						change="#StC" facs="#f026_z007" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no_caret"
						>.</add>
					<lb/>
					<del change="#StC" facs="#f026_z007" hand="#HM" rend="cut">unknown I infinite
						subject</del><metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f026_z006" function="guideline"
						place="overleaf" rend="guideline">guideline</metamark><add change="#StC"
						facs="#f026_z027" hand="#HM" place="below" rend="clip">Especially, as I
						somehow cling to the<lb/> strange fancy, that, in all men, hiddenly
						reside<lb/> certain wondrous, occult properties -- as in some <metamark
							change="#StC" facs="#f026_z005" function="caret" place="inline"
							rend="caret">caret</metamark></add><add change="#StC" facs="#f026_z003"
						hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">plants <reg facs="#f026_z004"
							>and</reg></add><add> minerals -- <lb/>which by some happy but very rare
						accident (as bronze was <lb/> discovered by the melting of the iron and
						brass in the burning of Corinth)<lb/> may chance to be called forth here on
						earth; not entirely <lb/>waiting for their better discovery in the more
						congenial, <lb/>blessed atmosphere of heaven.<lb/></add></p>
				<p>Once more -- for it is hard to be finite<lb/> upon an infinite subject, and all
						<metamark change="#StC" facs="#f026_z002" function="caret" place="inline"
						rend="caret">caret with guideline</metamark><add change="#StC"
						facs="#f026_z001" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">subjects </add><del
						change="#StC" facs="#f026_z000" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">things
					</del>are infinite.</p>
			</div>
		</body>
